I can’t believe 2022 is already gone! It’s been such a busy year for me. I documented over 30 Elopements and other shoots. Went to 8 countries and some of those more than once! Three of those ( Argentina, Norway & Portugal) were first times for me! I held 3 of my Expeditions with amazing people. And to top it all off our family moved from Arizona to Utah! I want to give a huge thank you to everyone that let me be part of their story this year! I’m forever humbled that you would let me take your pictures! Here’s to 2023! 

#2022recap #elopementphotographer #adventureelopementphotographer

Simply put my Expeditions are Adventure Elopement Workshops. The goal of each of my Expeditions is to teach you how to become a successful Adventure Elopement Photographer. We shoot together in amazing places with the best models. You will learn how I find locations, handle extreme conditions, how to pose and direct couples, edit and of course create stunning images! 

If you are looking for hands on education and a way to get your foot in the door of destination Elopements these workshops are for you! 

Follow the link in my bio for all the details!

My 2023 Iceland Expedition still has a few spots open! Don’t miss your chance to come to Iceland with me and shoot at some of my favorite locations! My Expeditions are a hands-on workshop for Elopement Photographers. During the Expedition you will get to shoot alongside me, take a 4x4 into the Highlands of Iceland and experience some of Iceland’s most unique landscapes! 
  This set of images was taken at my very first Iceland Expedition. We drove over 2 hours into the Highlands to get to this spot.  Only to have it raining on us when we got there. After waiting for a while to see if the rain would stop, we decided to just go for it! I’m so glad we did because these are some of my favorite images from that Expedition! 
  You can find all the details for my Iceland Expedition in my bio link! 

#tylerryeexpeditions #expeditionswithtylerrye #tylerryeworkshop

“We had our elopement photos in AZ and it was an amazing otherworldly experience. Our goal was to have photos where it looked like we were getting married on the Moon or Mars and Tyler suggested the perfect location that was not overcrowded and a true hidden gem. He brought us into the location with his pick up truck since the roads were filled with sand, which was very convenient and opens up many more possibilities for location. In terms of taking photos, Tyler really cares about the quality and look of the photos and isn't particular about sticking to a certain number or only giving you full res copies of certain chosen ones like some other photographers do.  My requests were a bit strange at times (like taking pictures of tadpoles we saw in the small pools of water) but Tyler gladly obliged. He's really chill and makes you feel at ease immediately. My partner and I are not the most natural when it comes to being in front of the camera but Tyler made it work and got some amazing shots. Overall, HIGHLY RECOMMEND and worth the cost. It's really an experience that we will remember for years to come.”
